tavaasKurpees.description:
Participating artists: Ance Dālmane, Ēriks Frišenfelds, Katrīna Kovaļuka, Katrīne Kate Kucina-Arbidāne, Sofija Mālniece, Maija Seņkova, Dagnis Stikāns.

The exhibition’s diverse artworks are united by their conceptual foundation – each work is based on a reference to another artist’s practice. The scope of references, rooted in each young artist’s individual interests, is wide: the focus of the work may be medium, theme, method, technique, materiality, attitude, or principle.

The works are a practical exercise and a personal attempt to learn by doing. We learn from each other, and the motivation to learn is natural curiosity, which manifests as interest in one another. To understand oneself, it is important to be aware of one's influences, to identify them, and to appreciate the inspiration provided by peers – as creativity is nothing but a new combination of accumulated knowledge, experience, and skills.

The exhibition is on view at RAA (@veldze.radosarupnica), Matīsa iela 8, from 12 to 18 July, daily from 16:00 to 19:00.

🥪 On Tuesday, 15 July, join us for a sandwich workshop with Katrīna and Katrīne!

The exhibition is organized by 3rd-year students of LMA KAS and Maija Kurševa in collaboration with the @raa_riga team.
Supported by LMA KAS VKN.
Exhibition friend: @sabrs_festival

